{"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClassInitFunc","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ClassInitFunc","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" = "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtype.h@T@GClassInitFunc","text":"GClassInitFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function should initialize all static class members."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The initialization process of a class involves:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Copying common members from the parent class over to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"derived class structure."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Zero initialization of the remaining members not copied"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"over from the parent class.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Invocation of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBaseInitFunc()"},{"text":" initializers of all parent","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types and the class’ type."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Invocation of the class’ "},{"code":"GClassInitFunc()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" initializer.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since derived classes are partially initialized through a memory copy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the parent class, the general rule is that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBaseInitFunc()"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBaseFinalizeFunc()"},{"type":"text","text":" should take care of necessary reinitialization"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and release of those class members that were introduced by the type"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that specified these "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBaseInitFunc()``\/GBaseFinalizeFunc()"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClassInitFunc()"},{"text":" should only care about initializing static","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"class members, while dynamic class members (such as allocated strings"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or reference counted resources) are better handled by a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBaseInitFunc()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for this type, so proper initialization of the dynamic class members"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is performed for class initialization of derived types as well.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An example may help to correspond the intend of the different class","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initializers:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"syntax":"C","code":["typedef struct {","  GObjectClass parent_class;","  gint         static_integer;","  gchar       *dynamic_string;","} TypeAClass;","static void","type_a_base_class_init (TypeAClass *class)","{","  class->dynamic_string = g_strdup (\"some string\");","}","static void","type_a_base_class_finalize (TypeAClass *class)","{","  g_free (class->dynamic_string);","}","static void","type_a_class_init (TypeAClass *class)","{","  class->static_integer = 42;","}","","typedef struct {","  TypeAClass   parent_class;","  gfloat       static_float;","  GString     *dynamic_gstring;","} TypeBClass;","static void","type_b_base_class_init (TypeBClass *class)","{","  class->dynamic_gstring = g_string_new (\"some other string\");","}","static void","type_b_base_class_finalize (TypeBClass *class)","{","  g_string_free (class->dynamic_gstring);","}","static void","type_b_class_init (TypeBClass *class)","{","  class->static_float = 3.14159265358979323846;","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Initialization of TypeBClass will first cause initialization of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"TypeAClass (derived classes reference their parent classes, see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_type_class_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" on this)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Initialization of TypeAClass roughly involves zero-initializing its fields,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then calling its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBaseInitFunc()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type_a_base_class_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" to allocate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its dynamic members (dynamic_string), and finally calling its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClassInitFunc()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type_a_class_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" to initialize its static members (static_integer)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The first step in the initialization process of TypeBClass is then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a plain memory copy of the contents of TypeAClass into TypeBClass and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"zero-initialization of the remaining fields in TypeBClass.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The dynamic members of TypeAClass within TypeBClass now need"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reinitialization which is performed by calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type_a_base_class_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with an argument of TypeBClass."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After that, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBaseInitFunc()"},{"text":" of TypeBClass, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type_b_base_class_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is called to allocate the dynamic members of TypeBClass (dynamic_gstring),","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and finally the "},{"code":"GClassInitFunc()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" of TypeBClass, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type_b_class_init()"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is called to complete the initialization process with the static members"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(static_float).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Corresponding finalization counter parts to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBaseInitFunc()"},{"type":"text","text":" functions"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have to be provided to release allocated resources at class finalization","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"time.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/classinitfunc"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ClassInitFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"typealias","roleHeading":"Type Alias","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"title":"ClassInitFunc","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ClassInitFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject13ClassInitFunca"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A callback function used by the type system to initialize the class"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of a specific type."}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"abstract":[],"title":"GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ClassInitFunc":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClassInitFunc","type":"topic","role":"symbol","title":"ClassInitFunc","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/classinitfunc","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ClassInitFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ClassInitFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A callback function used by the type system to initialize the class"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a specific type."}]}}}